# NorthStar Development Rules

## Code Style
- Python 3.10+ with type hints throughout
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- Pydantic v2 models with ConfigDict(from_attributes=True)
- Keep functions focused and under 50 lines where possible

## Architecture
- All engines are async classes with clear single responsibilities
- State persistence through StateManager only (no direct SQLite access)
- LLM calls always go through LLMClient/NullLLMClient abstraction
- CLI commands use asyncio.run() bridge pattern

## Testing
- Every module has corresponding tests in tests/unit/
- Use NullLLMClient for all unit tests (no real API calls)
- Use tmp_path fixture for filesystem tests
- pytest with asyncio_mode="auto"

## Priority Stack
- Focus on correctness of scoring formulas first
- Drift detection thresholds must match config exactly
- All models must support JSON round-trip serialization
